  <summary date="2004-02-19T21:34:49Z" status="Introduced in House">Calls upon the Government of France to respect the right of individuals to practice their religion freely and to display insignia of their faith.

Joins the U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom in recommending that the U.S. Government urge the Government of France to reassess its initiative banning conspicuous religious articles and symbols in state schools.</summary>
